Control Structures in C : These are the statements that specify the "Flow of Control" in a progress

Statements has three types
1. Sequential
2. Selection/Branching 
3. Iterative (Loops) => do-while, while, for

Selection/Branching has two types
1. Conditional => if, switch
2. Unconditional => goto, break, continue, return

Selection -- Choosing from a set of alternatives
Branching -- Transferring the ocntrol from one location of a program to another
Iterative -- Repeated execution of statements.
